The night before an English
one, an online cramming session

00:30:54.280 --> 00:30:56.390
with a writer?

00:30:56.390 --> 00:30:59.600
So many, many possibilities.

00:30:59.600 --> 00:31:02.220
No pressure here, and this is
the point I'm gonna finish on.

00:31:05.720 --> 00:31:08.430
For teenagers in
particular, the internet

00:31:08.430 --> 00:31:10.700
is so much more
than time and space.

00:31:10.700 --> 00:31:14.360
It's where they learn,
where they're entertained,

00:31:14.360 --> 00:31:17.950
where they're looking for
a guide to the future,

00:31:17.950 --> 00:31:20.600
and maybe it needs to be
filled with more spaces

00:31:20.600 --> 00:31:23.130
to innovate, and to
learn, and to inspire,

00:31:23.130 --> 00:31:26.900
because companies
like this have become

00:31:26.900 --> 00:31:28.610
some of the most
powerful in the world,

00:31:28.610 --> 00:31:32.400
and all I would say is,
with great power comes

00:31:32.400 --> 00:31:34.120
great responsibility.

00:31:34.120 --> 00:31:36.030
And I wanted to leave
it with a final note

00:31:36.030 --> 00:31:39.615
