00:49:27.010 --> 00:49:30.990
And teenagers are so used to
be being talked at and about

00:49:30.990 --> 00:49:32.946
that no one ever sits
and says, well, tell me.

00:49:32.946 --> 00:49:35.070
Tell me, well, how did you
feel when your mum died?

00:49:35.070 --> 00:49:37.490
How did you feel when you
got kicked out of school?

00:49:37.490 --> 00:49:40.472
How did you feel when
you got into Oxford?

00:49:40.472 --> 00:49:41.930
And all these
stories are in there,

00:49:41.930 --> 00:49:43.138
and I think that's the thing.

00:49:43.138 --> 00:49:45.430
It's communication
and collaboration.

00:49:45.430 --> 00:49:48.407
Rather than say, these
are the teen problems,

00:49:48.407 --> 00:49:50.240
you say, you tell me
what teen problems are,

00:49:50.240 --> 00:49:52.475
and let's sort this problem
out togetherness, and let's try

00:49:52.475 --> 00:49:53.724
and come up with some answers.

00:49:53.724 --> 00:49:55.860
And I think that that's
pertinent for what we're

00:49:55.860 --> 00:49:57.410
doing on the
internet, how we deal

00:49:57.410 --> 00:49:59.390
with quite a lot of
the internet problems,

00:49:59.390 --> 00:50:03.950
and just generally how we're
going to improve as a species.

00:50:03.950 --> 00:50:06.280
That's a profound note
to end on, wasn't it?

